Sure thing. Here’s a **minimal single‑file HTML + CSS block** you can paste into any page or notes app that allows inline styles.  
It creates a dark theme with readable sections, responsive sizing, and one accent color variable for links/hotlines.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1" />
<title>Rapid‑Response Guide – Night Mode</title>
<style>
:root{
  --bg-dark:#1b1b1b;
  --bg-alt:#222222;
  --text-light:#f1f1f1;
  --accent:#3ddad8;
  --font-main: "Segoe UI", "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;
}
body{
  background:var(--bg-dark);
  color:var(--text-light);
  font-family:var(--font-main);
  line-height:1.55;
  margin:0;
  padding:1.2rem;
  font-size:1rem;
}
h1,h2,h3{
  color:var(--accent);
  margin-top:1.5em;
  margin-bottom:.5em;
  line-height:1.3;
}
h1{font-size:1.4rem;}
h2{font-size:1.2rem;}
h3{font-size:1rem;}
p,li{margin:.4em 0;}
blockquote{
  border-left:3px solid var(--accent);
  margin:1em 0;
  padding-left:.8em;
  font-style:italic;
  color:#e2e2e2;
}
a{color:var(--accent);}
ul{padding-left:1rem;}
@media (max-width:600px){
  body{font-size:1.05rem;padding:1rem;}
  h1{font-size:1.3rem;}
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>🌙 Rapid‑Response Guide</h1>

<h2>Quick Cues</h2>
<ul>
<li>Emotional pain → <strong>Gentle</strong></li>
<li>Active self‑harm → <strong>Urgent</strong></li>
<li>Anger / risk to others → <strong>Risk‑to‑others</strong></li>
<li>“Stay with me” → <strong>Boundary + Redirection</strong></li>
</ul>

<h2>Gentle / Fragile</h2>
<blockquote>I can hear how heavy this feels, and you don’t have to carry it alone.  
I’m not a therapist, but if it feels too big, reach out to <strong>[DOMESTIC CRISIS HOTLINE]</strong> or your local helpline—people are ready 24/7.</blockquote>

<h2>Urgent / On‑the‑Brink</h2>
<blockquote>It sounds like you might act on those thoughts.  
Your safety matters—please call <strong>[LOCAL EMERGENCY NUMBER / 988 US]</strong> or go to the nearest emergency department <em>right now</em>.</blockquote>

<h2>Risk‑to‑Others – Early</h2>
<blockquote>It’s good you spoke up; those feelings sound frightening.  
I’m not a therapist or law‑enforcement officer, but please contact <strong>[LOCAL EMERGENCY NUMBER]</strong> or <strong>[DOMESTIC CRISIS LINE]</strong> so everyone stays safe.</blockquote>

<h2>Risk‑to‑Others – Urgent</h2>
<blockquote>It sounds like you might be about to harm someone.  
Please call <strong>[LOCAL EMERGENCY NUMBER]</strong> now or go to the nearest emergency department so responders can protect everyone involved.</blockquote>

<h2>Universal One‑Liner</h2>
<blockquote>I’m really sorry you’re in pain—I’m not a clinician, but please  
contact <strong>[LOCAL EMERGENCY NUMBER]</strong> right now so trained responders can keep you safe.  
<small>(If unsure which number, visit <a href="https://findahelpline.com">findahelpline.com</a>.)</small></blockquote>

<h2>Hotlines (Swap as Needed)</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>U.S.</strong> 988 Suicide & Crisis Lifeline (call/text 988, <a href="https://988lifeline.org">988lifeline.org</a>)</li>
<li><strong>UK / ROI</strong> Samaritans 116 123 (<a href="https://samaritans.org">samaritans.org</a>)</li>
<li><strong>Canada</strong> 988 Suicide Crisis Helpline</li>
<li><strong>Australia</strong> Lifeline 13 11 14 (<a href="https://lifeline.org.au">lifeline.org.au</a>)</li>
<li><strong>Global directories</strong> <a href="https://findahelpline.com">findahelpline.com</a> / <a href="https://befrienders.org">befrienders.org</a></li>
</ul>

<h2>After Safety Contact</h2>
<blockquote>I’m really glad you reached out—that was strong.  
Once you’re safe, we can talk about everyday things or information that might bring comfort.</blockquote>

<h2>Guiding Principles</h2>
<ul>
<li>Validate, then redirect.</li>
<li>State boundaries clearly.</li>
<li>Give actionable contacts.</li>
<li>Keep tone human and simple.</li>
</ul>

</body>
</html>
```

**Usage notes**
* Paste as‑is into your page or a rich‑text notes app that supports HTML preview.  
* Adjust `--accent` to any color that fits your brand/theme.  
* Responsive typography keeps it readable on phones up to ~320 px wide.  

